All 5 tests pass. Now I will proceed with the systematic refactoring evaluation.

## Step 1: Naming Evaluation (FIRST PRIORITY)

**Naming Evaluation**:

| Name | Purpose | Assessment |
|------|---------|------------|
| `nextGeneration` | Computes the next generation of live cells in Game of Life | Excellent -- directly reflects the Game of Life domain concept |
| `countLiveNeighbors` | Counts how many of a cell's 8 neighbors are alive | Clear and descriptive |
| `liveCells` | Input array of live cell coordinates | Good domain name |
| `alive` | Set of serialized live cell keys for O(1) lookup | Acceptable, though `aliveSet` or `liveCellKeys` might be marginally clearer |
| `survivors` | Cells that survive to the next generation | Good domain term |
| `deadCandidates` | Dead cells adjacent to live cells that might be born | Clear |
| `born` | Dead cells that gain exactly 3 neighbors and come alive | Good domain term |
| `key` | String representation of a coordinate | Generic but contextually clear |

Assessment: All names are strong domain terms. No rename warranted at this point.

